        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The `definition` field use `desc` value only when `cmd` is of the function type,  if `cmd` is of the string type, `definition` serves a meaningful purpose.  eg:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\napi.nvim_create_user_command('WithDesc',  'echo \"hi\"', { desc = 'Says hi' })\r\nlocal res = api.nvim_get_commands({builtin=false}).WithDesc\r\nres.def = 'echo \"hi\"'\r\nres.desc =  'Says hi'\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-05-06T10:51:28Z",
